    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-11-25T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-11-25T20:00:00-05:00" n="791"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d791">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/11290: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Second Secretary of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atcheson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-11-26T09:00:00+08:00"
                            >November 26, 1937—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 9:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>958. Embassy’s 944, November 22, 10 p.m., Nanking safety zone. German Embassy
                    here under date November 23rd requested German <pb facs="0728" n="721"
                        xml:id="pg_721"/> Consulate General [at] Shanghai (1) to communicate
                    Committee’s proposal to local Japanese authorities and unofficially but
                    warmheartedly support it on humanitarian grounds and (2) to ask German Embassy
                    [at] Tokyo enter similar action. Under date 25th German Chairman of the
                    Committee sent an appeal to Chancellor Hitler and former Shanghai Consul General
                    Krieber that they interest themselves in the proposal and say a good word for it
                    to the Japanese Government.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Ambassador, Peiping, Shanghai. Peiping kindly repeat to Tokyo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Atcheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
